#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:14-2
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Navigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm+html.body.h1:14-2"
msgid "Navigation Quick Key Manager"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:15-2
msgid ""
"Navigation Quick Keys are single or combination keystrokes that let you move "
"quickly around Web pages, Acrobat PDF files, Microsoft Word documents, or "
"Microsoft Outlook e-mail messages. For example, if you press the letter "
"<strong>H</strong> while visiting a Web page, JAWS jumps to and reads the "
"next heading on the page. Likewise, if you press <strong>SHIFT+H</strong>, "
"JAWS jumps to and reads the previous heading."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:16-2
msgid ""
"Use the Navigation Quick Key Manager to view current key assignments, <a "
"href=\"#Edit\">edit key assignments</a>, or <a href=\"#Delete\">delete key "
"assignments</a>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:17-2
msgid "Opening the Navigation Quick Key Manager"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-2
msgid "To open the Navigation Quick Key Manager, do one of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:20-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>INSERT+F2</strong>, <strong>N</strong>, and then "
"<strong>ENTER</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:22-4
msgid ""
"From the JAWS application window, press <strong>ALT+U</strong> to open the "
"Utilities menu, press <strong>N</strong> to jump to the Navigation Quick Key "
"manager, and then press <strong>H</strong> to open HTML/PDF Keys, <strong>O</"
"strong> to open Microsoft Outlook Keys, or <strong>W</strong> to open "
"Microsoft Word Keys."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:24-2
msgid ""
"A list of all Navigation Quick Keys for Web pages and PDF documents, Outlook "
"e-mail messages, or for Word documents appear in the open dialog box. Use "
"the <strong>UP</strong> and <strong>DOWN ARROW</strong> keys to scroll "
"through the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:25-2
msgid "Editing Key Assignments"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:26-2
msgid ""
"You can assign an unused letter or number to an action listed in the "
"Navigation Quick Key column of the dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-2
msgid "To assign a key to an action, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:29-4
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Navigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm+html.body.ol.li:29-4"
msgid ""
"Press the <strong>UP</strong> or <strong>DOWN ARROW</strong> key to move to "
"an action in the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:30-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the Edit Key Assignment button and "
"press <strong>SPACEBAR</strong>. The Edit Quick Navigation Key Assignment "
"dialog box opens."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:31-4
msgid ""
"In the Key Assignment combo box, press <strong>UP ARROW </strong> or "
"<strong>DOWN ARROW</strong> to scroll through the list of available letters "
"and numbers that can be assigned to the action. Press <strong>ENTER</strong> "
"after choosing an item from the list. The new key assignment now appears in "
"the Assignment column of the Navigation Quick Key Manager dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:32-4
msgid ""
"To save the change, move to the OK button in the Navigation Quick Key "
"Manager dialog box, and press <strong>ENTER</strong>. The new assignment "
"takes place immediately."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:34-2
msgid "Deleting Key Assignments"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:35-2
msgid "To remove a Navigation Quick Key from an action, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:37-4
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Navigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm+html.body.ol.li:37-4"
msgid ""
"Press the <strong>UP</strong> or <strong>DOWN ARROW</strong> key to move to "
"an action in the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:38-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the Delete Key Assignment button and "
"press <strong>SPACEBAR</strong>. The word Unassigned appears next to the key "
"action in the Navigation Quick Key Manager dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:39-4
msgid ""
"To save the change, move to the OK button, and press <strong>ENTER</strong>. "
"The change takes place immediately."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:41-2
msgid ""
"Refer to <a href=\"popapps.chm::/internet/internet_explorer_5/"
"qk_nav_ie.htm\">Navigation Quick Keys</a> for a list of quick keys that you "
"can use with Web pages and PDF documents."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CNavigation_Quick_Key_Manager.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:42-2
msgid ""
"Refer to <a href=\"popapps.chm::/word_processing/microsoft_word/"
"Navigation_Quick_Keys_in_Word.htm#Nav_Quick_Keys\">Navigation Quick Keys in "
"Word</a> for a list of quick keys to use with Word documents."
msgstr ""
